snippet.textDisplay: We won't go down, I have to say I was worried but under Stendel we are slowly improving. Played well against Aberdeen in our last home league game, and stepped things up a notch for the game yesterday. It's about time we started making Tynecastle a tough place for teams to visit again, Levein had spread the rot around the club, so glad he's gone. Apparently we are still to make 2 to 4 signings before the end of the window so I'm confident by the end of January we will have a much better balanced squad. We actually have a striker who looks like he can score goals, finally. With the right service he can be a 20 goal a season striker as he proved with Ross County. Obviously not this season as it's nearly February, but I still reckon he can hit double figures by the end of this season.
